# Terms of Use

This document outlines the terms of use for the "Task Scheduling in Distributed Memory Multi-core Real-Time Embedded Systems Simulator" project hosted on this GitHub repository.

## Licensing

All code in this repository is licensed under the MIT License unless otherwise specified. This license allows for modification and reuse of the code for both personal and commercial use. However, it requires that the original copyright notice and license be included in all copies or substantial portions of the software. Please see the `LICENSE` file in this repository for more details.

## Citation

If you use the software or any part of it for academic or research purposes, you are requested to provide proper attribution by citing the following publication:

[R] S. Alshaer, C. Lua, P. Muoka, D. Onwuchekwa and R. Obermaisser,
"Graph Neural Networks Based Meta-scheduling in Adaptive Time-Triggered Systems," 
2022 IEEE 27th International Conference on Emerging Technologies and Factory Automation (ETFA), 
Stuttgart, Germany, 2022, pp. 1-6, doi: 10.1109/ETFA52439.2022.9921580.

In addition, we kindly ask you to reference this GitHub repository in your work. 

## Conduct

We strive to foster a welcoming and inclusive community for everyone who wishes to use, contribute to, or discuss this project. Therefore, we expect that users of this repository will respect the rights and dignity of others, and will refrain from any behavior that could be considered harassment or discrimination.

Please note that we reserve the right to remove, edit, or reject issues, comments, commits, code, and other contributions that are not aligned with these Terms of Use, or to temporarily or permanently ban any user for other behaviors that are deemed inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.

For more details, please refer to the `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md` file in this repository (if available).

